  "text": "The dependent variable in our analyses was depression, as measured by the EURO-D scale. This depressive symptoms scale was developed to allow for a valid comparison of mental health between European countries, and it is based on 12 items related to depression, pessimism, feelings of guilt, irritability, wishing for death, sleep, interests, appetite, fatigue, concentration, enjoyment, or tearfulness [CITATION_1] .",
